The evidence with the title 'Nuclear power in the United States - Wikipedia ' says Nuclear power in the United States is provided by 99 commercial reactors with a net capacity of 100,350 megawatts ( mw ) , 65 pressurized water reactors and 34 boiling water reactors.In 2016 they produced a total of 805.3 terawatt-hours of electricity , which accounted for 19.7% of the nation's total electric energy generation .  ... . By the mid-1970s it became clear that nuclear power would not grow nearly  ... 
